The paper proposes a reinforcement learning-based approach for cost-sensitive learning, which involves the acquisition of input features with specific costs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The approach also involves representation learning, which is a common technique in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) tasks. Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques for minimizing inference cost, which is a common problem in Data Structures (cs.DS).
